<score-partwise>
  <work>
    <work-title>How Firm A Foundation</work-title>
  </work>
  <identification>
    <creator type="composer">Words: John Rippon, 1787.
Music: 'Foundation (Funk)' or 'Protection' Joseph Funk, 1832.  Setting: "Union Harmony", 1837.
copyright: public domain.  This score is a part of the Open Hymnal Project, 2007 Revision.</creator>
    <encoding>
      <encoder>abc2xml version 268</encoder>
      <software>https://wim.vree.org/svgParse/abc2xml.html</software>
      <encoding-date>2026-07-21</encoding-date>
    </encoding>
    <source>Music source: CCEL</source>
    <miscellaneous>
      <miscellaneous-field name="lyrics">6.Even down to old age all My people shall prove
My sovereign, eternal, unchangeable love;
And when hoary hairs shall their temples adorn,
Like lambs they shall still in My bosom be borne.

7.The soul that on Jesus has leaned for repose,
I will not, I will not desert to its foes;
That soul, though all hell should endeavor to shake,
I'll never, no never, no never forsake.</miscellaneous-field>
    </miscellaneous>
  </identification>
